      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Some new fallen snow is falling on a snow surface that is powdery in the shade and crusted can form on the sunny side. In the upper metre of the snowpack, weak intermediate layers below a thin ice lense and graupel are embedded in places. In windward areas, the snow is bonded and prone to triggering. The snowpack base is compact and largely stable. Deep-lying layers of faceted crystals are difficult to disturb. On the south side, the snow is often wet towards the ground. Sliding movements on smooth ground are possible."
